  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"Are you game?\"",
  "response": "The phrase **\"Are you game?\"** is an informal way of asking someone if they are **willing** or **interested in doing something**, especially if it involves a challenge, adventure, or something new. It\u2019s like asking, \"Are you up for it?\" or \"Do you want to give it a try?\" \n\nFor example:\n- \"We\u2019re going skydiving this weekend\u2014are you game?\"\n- \"I\u2019m thinking of trying that spicy food challenge\u2014are you game?\"\n\nIt implies enthusiasm and a spirit of participation.",
